{"root":{"children":[{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"You can't teach what you don't know, and you can't know what you're not constantly learning yourself. The half-life of technical knowledge is shrinking, and yesterday's breakthrough is tomorrow's baseline.","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"type":"audio","version":1,"duration":867.744,"mimeType":"audio/mpeg","src":"__GHOST_URL__/content/media/2025/02/Automated-YouTube-Content-Analysis-with-Trigger--1-.mp3","title":"[NotepadLM] Fingers On The Pulse w/Trigger.dev","thumbnailSrc":"https://blog.withseismic.com/content/media/2025/02/Automated-YouTube-Content-Analysis-with-Trigger--1-_thumb.png"},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"This challenge isn't unique to me—it's something Fabian and his team at [Redacted] were determined to solve. As a learning platform, they needed to ensure their educational content remained relevant, fresh, and aligned with industry trends. ","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Their goal was to create content that truly followed the zeitgeist and promoted progression by keeping up with everything happening in the digital space.","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"type":"image","version":1,"src":"__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2025/02/image-5.png","width":1664,"height":1125,"title":"","alt":"","caption":"<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Fingers on the pulse at all time: Gleaning deep insights from thousands of videos </span>","cardWidth":"regular","href":""},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"The Problem: Always Six Months Behind","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"extended-heading","version":1,"tag":"h2"},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"The traditional content research workflow most content teams are using has fundamental flaws:","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"children":[{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Massive time investment","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":": Content researchers spent 60% of their time just trying to stay current","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":1},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Inconsistent analysis","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":": Different researchers extracted different insights from the same content","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":2},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Limited coverage","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":": They could only monitor about 25 channels regularly","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":3},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"High latency","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":": Content in specific sectors lagged, anywhere from 3-6 months behind cutting-edge topics; a no-go when dealing with the latest LLM tooling and models.","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":4},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Subjective prioritization","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":": Topic selection was based on what "felt" important rather than data — not a problem for the team and their refined taste, but lacking a system to move faster. ","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":5}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"list","version":1,"listType":"bullet","start":1,"tag":"ul"},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Fabian's team knew they didn't want to continue with manual methods and accept the risks of being perpetually behind. They needed to find a technical solution to automate their research process.","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Why We Chose Trigger.dev: Simplifying Distributed Processing","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"extended-heading","version":1,"tag":"h2"},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"From previous projects, I've spent countless nights wrestling with job queues. Most developers have horror stories about production queue systems going down at 3 AM because Redis ran out of memory, or jobs silently failing because no one (","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":2,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"ahem","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":") set up proper dead-letter queues. You know the pain if you've ever built a system that needs to process thousands of anything.","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"For this project, we chose Trigger.dev from the start, which proved to be an A* decision. Instead of spending weeks setting up infrastructure, we could focus entirely on solving the content analysis problem. Trigger.dev offered:","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"children":[{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Built-in queue management","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":": No need to manage our own Redis instances or job persistence","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":1},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Native batch processing","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":": Support for processing hundreds of items in parallel","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":2},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Concurrency controls","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":": Fine-grained control to prevent API rate limiting","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":3},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Robust error handling","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":": Automatic retries and detailed error reporting","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":4},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Development simplicity","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":": Focus on business logic rather than infrastructure","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":5}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"list","version":1,"listType":"bullet","start":1,"tag":"ul"},{"type":"image","version":1,"src":"__GHOST_URL__/content/images/2025/02/image.png","width":1847,"height":1271,"title":"","alt":"A screenshot of Trigger.dev task workflow","caption":"<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">Job Queues Never Looked This Good Thanks To Trigger.dev</span>","cardWidth":"regular","href":""},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Our implementation was refreshingly straightforward:","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"type":"codeblock","version":1,"code":"export const processYouTubeChannels = task({
  id: "process-youtube-channels",
  maxDuration: 600,
  run: async (payload: ProcessYouTubeChannelsPayload) => {
    // Create batch payloads for each channel
    const channelPayloads = payload.channels.map((channel) => ({
      payload: { youtubeUrl: channel },
      options: {
        queue: {
          name: "youtube-channels",
          concurrency: 5,
        },
      },
    }));

    // Batch trigger channel scraping
    const batchResult = await scrapeYouTubeProfile.batchTrigger(channelPayloads);

    return {
      success: true,
      tasksTriggered: batchResult.runs.length,
    };
  },
});
","language":"javascript","caption":""},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"By offloading the DevOps complexity to Trigger.dev's team (who are incredible at what they do), we could focus on building the solution that Fabian's team needed. Trigger.dev has been a fantastic resource throughout this project and I thoroughly recommend baking it into your workflows like ours.","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"The One-Week Proof of Concept: Testing the Waters","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"extended-heading","version":1,"tag":"h2"},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"This project was designed as a one-week proof of concept sprint. The reason we do these short sprints is pretty simple: it allows clients to quickly determine whether an idea has legs without committing to an entire build. In a very short time, Fabian and his team could test the waters, see what life is like in the automation lane, and decide after some rigorous testing whether it was the solution for them or if we should go back and try something else.","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Our proof of concept focused on building a core pipeline architecture:","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"children":[{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Channel Discovery","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":": Monitors YouTube channels and detects new videos","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":1},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Video Processing","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":": Extracts transcripts and metadata from each video","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":2},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Content Analysis","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":": Uses AI to extract structured insights from the transcript","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":3},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Insight Storage","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":": Organizes and stores the processed insights","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":4},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Content Retrieval","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":": Provides filtered access to processed content by various criteria","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":5}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"list","version":1,"listType":"number","start":1,"tag":"ol"},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"This approach allowed us to demonstrate the potential of automation without building a complete end-to-end solution.","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Multi-level Batch Processing: The Key to Scalability","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"extended-heading","version":1,"tag":"h2"},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"One of the key technical innovations in our system is the use of multi-level batch processing for efficient scaling:","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"children":[{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Level 1: Process multiple channels concurrently","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":1},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Level 2: For each channel, process multiple videos concurrently","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":2}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"list","version":1,"listType":"bullet","start":1,"tag":"ul"},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"This approach allows us to process hundreds of videos simultaneously, dramatically reducing the time required to extract insights:","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"children":[{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Manual approach: 200 videos × 30 minutes per video = 100 hours (or 2.5 work weeks)","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":1},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Our system: 200 videos processed in parallel = ~30 minutes total","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":2}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"list","version":1,"listType":"bullet","start":1,"tag":"ul"},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"This ","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":1,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"200x ","type":"extended-text","version":1},{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"speedup demonstrates how automation could transform the content research process for Fabian's team.","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"extended-quote","version":1},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"AI-Powered Content Analysis: Structured Insights","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"extended-heading","version":1,"tag":"h2"},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"The core of our insight extraction uses AI to analyze video transcripts and extract structured information:","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"For each video, we extract:","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"children":[{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Talking Points: Key topics discussed in the content","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":1},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Category: Primary content category (Technology, Business, etc.)","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":2},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Summary: Concise overview of the content","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":3},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Keywords: Relevant terms and concepts","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":4},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Learnings: Actionable insights users can apply","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"listitem","version":1,"value":5}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"list","version":1,"listType":"bullet","start":1,"tag":"ul"},{"children":[{"detail":0,"format":0,"mode":"normal","style":"","text":"Our initial implementation used a much simpler prompt that just asked for a summary and keywords. The results were disappointing—vague, generic summaries that didn't capture the technical depth needed. After several iterations, we landed on a more structured approach:","type":"extended-text","version":1}],"direction":"ltr","format":"","indent":0,"type":"paragraph","version":1},{"type":"codeblock","version":1,"code":"const response = await generateObject({
  model: openai("gpt-4o"),
  schema: z.object({
    talkingPoints: z.array(z.string()),
    category: z.string(),
